    <ul>
      <li>Onset: When did the confusion start?
        <ul>
          <li>Sudden</li>
          <ul>
            can have a renal cause but have to rule out other causes
            <li>After a head injury</li>
            <li>After a stroke</li>
            <li>After a seizure</li>
            <li>etc...</li>
          </ul>
          <li>Gradual</li>
          <ul>
            can have a renal cause but have to rule out other causes
            <li>After a head injury</li>
            <li>Dementia</li>
            <li>etc...</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Duration: How long has the confusion been present?</li>
      <li>A/R:</li>
      <ol>
        <li>Aggravated by:</li>
        <ol>
          <li>Triggers: ppt?</li>
          <li>anti histamines</li>
          <li>opiods</li>
          <li>Sleed aids</li>
        </ol>
        <li>Relieved by:</li>
      </ol>
      <li>Character/Type:</li>
      <ol>
        <li>Agitated</li>
        <li>Memory loss</li>
        <li>Disoriented</li>
        <li>Delirious</li>
        <li>drowsy</li>
      </ol>
      <li>Radiation:</li>
      <li>Associated Symptoms:</li>
      <ul>
        <li>CNS</li>
        <ul>
          <li>Seizures</li>
          <li>memory loss</li>
        </ul>
        <li>UTI</li>
        <ul>
          <li>fever</li>
          <li>Decreased urine output</li>
        </ul>
        <li>CVS</li>
        <ul>
          <li>Swelling of legs</li>
          <li>SOB</li>
        </ul>
        <li>Resp</li>
        <ul>
          <li>fever</li>
          <li>cough</li>
          <li>SOB</li>
        </ul>
        <li><em>Constipation</em></li>
        <li>Nausea/vomiting</li>
      </ul>
      <li>Progression: Has the confusion been getting worse?</li>
      <li>Pattern: </li>
      <ul>
        <li>Constant or</li>
        <li>intermittent?</li>
        <ul>
          <li>delirium</li>
        </ul>
      </ul>
      <li>E: Effect on life</li>
      <li>R: Red flag</li>
      <ul>
        <li>FAST </li>
        <li>Meningitis </li>
        <ul>
          <li>Rash</li>
          <li>fever</li>
          <li>headache</li>
          <li>neck stiffness</li>
        </ul>
        <li><br>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <li>S: severity scale</li>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>AMTS,</strong></li>
        <li><strong>4AT</strong></li>
        <li><strong>CAM)</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </ul>
